<TITLE> DGHS braces for any casualty </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 15 (bdnews24.com) -- The Directorate General of Health Services has taken special measures to deal with any casualty in the onslaughts of the cyclone in coastal districts, officials said Thursday. Dr Moazzem Hossain, director of disease control, told bdnews24.com that he had sent directives to all civil surgeons and divisional health officials Thursday afternoon to mobilise maximum resources. "I have asked district officials to form medical teams on an emergency basis to rush medical support to the cyclone-hit areas. I have also asked the officials to send medicines to the coastal districts for quick distribution," Moazzem said. The health directorate also cancelled all leave applications of health officials and staff members to facilitate emergency medical support. Meanwhile, the directorate also said it had sent "enough" water-purifying tablets to the disaster-prone areas to cope with any drinking water shortage. bd
